OL,3,C'Porch pirates' on the rise: What
OL,4,Cshould you do if your parcel is stolen?
OL,6,FIf you opted to have your parcel
OL,7,Fdelivered to a safe place and it was
OL,8,Fstolen, then it is your
OL,9,Fresponsibility, according to Compare
OL,10,Fthe Market.
OL,12,FHowever, if the courier left the
OL,13,Fparcel in a place you didn't agree to,
OL,14,Fand it was stolen, the responsibility
OL,15,Flies with the retailer.
OL,17,FSpeak to your credit card provider
